  "original_title": "\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bc8 \u0b95\u0bbf\u0bb3\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbf\u0baf '\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bbf' \u0b86\u0bb5\u0ba3\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "'Kali' Documentary That Raised Controversy",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Indian Embassy in Canada has said that the documentary 'Kali', which has been released as an insult to the Hindu God, should be withdrawn.",
        "The poster of documentary film 'Kali', directed by documentary film director Leena Manimekala, has created a lot of controversy.",
        "The poster depicts Hindu deity Maha Kali smoking a cigarette and holding the flag of the LGBT community in one hand.",
        "People are strongly protesting against this poster which has been published as an insult to the Hindu God.",
        "A festival called \"Rhythms of Canada\" was held at the Aga Khan Museum in Toronto, Canada to celebrate multiculturalism.",
        "A documentary film 'Kali' was screened as part of the festival. In this situation, the Indian Embassy in Ottawa has requested the withdrawal of the controversial 'Kali' documentary.",
        "In a statement, Hindu religious leaders in Canada have received complaints that a poster for a documentary screened as part of the 'Under the Tent' program at the Aga Khan Museum insulted a Hindu god."
      ],
